author: Associated Press and KIRO 7 staff
title: Sheriff: 6 injured in Priest Rapids Dam explosion
text:
Officials with the Grant Public Utility District say six employees have been injured in an explosion at Priest Rapids Dam on the Columbia River.
Utility district spokesman Thomas Stredwick says the employees were injured Thursday afternoon in a possible electrical explosion at the dam near Mattawa.
The six have various levels of injuries with some flown to area hospitals and others transported by ambulance for treatment.
#BREAKING : Harborview Medical Ctr in Seattle is expecting 2 patients fr the Priest Rapids Dam explosion. More on KIRO 7
â€” KIRO 7 (@KIRO7Seattle) October 9, 2015 On Thursday night, Harborview Medical Center advised they were expecting two of the patients from the explosion.
Multiple agencies have responded to the incident including the Hanford Fire Department.
Officials say the structure of the dam is stable and no one down the river is at risk.
